<item>
            <title>[LU-11429] MDT parameter enable_remote_dir should be renamed</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11429</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://doc.lustre.org/lustre_manual.xhtml#dbdoclet.lfsmkdir&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://doc.lustre.org/lustre_manual.xhtml#dbdoclet.lfsmkdir&lt;/a&gt; specifies that enable_remote_dir can be used to control whether remote sub-directories can be created off of any MDT.  However, the control appears to have been removed with &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-3537&quot; title=&quot;allow cross-MDT for all metadata operations &quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-3537&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-3537&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, but the interface wasn&apos;t removed.  When this code changes, an LUDOC update will be necessary.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="53423">LU-11429</key>
            <summary>MDT parameter enable_remote_dir should be renamed</summary>
