Commit: 32b0004ef1c34347e4d312b9126496db50634ee0&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="234062" author="adilger" created="Thu, 27 Sep 2018 11:45:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;As far as I can see, &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-3537&quot; title=&quot;allow cross-MDT for all metadata operations &quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-3537&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-3537&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is only removing the restriction on cross-MDT rename and cross-MDT hard links.  The &lt;tt&gt;enable_remote_dir&lt;/tt&gt; parameter still exists and is checked in the code where cross-MDT operations are performed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve pushed a patch to clean up the code a bit to make the function naming consistent with the tunable names.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
